Bell Canada, a unit of Bell CanadaEnterprises Inc &lt;BCE>, said it applied for an average eight pctcut in Canadian long distance rates.    The application to the Canadian Radio-television andTelecommunications Commission would also reduce the initialperiod for operated-assisted calls from three minutes to oneminute and operator- and customer-dialed calls would be chargedthe same.    The billing of operator-assisted calls would include aconection charge, however. The new rate structure is similar toschedules announced by Bell January 1 for calls within Ontario,Quebec and parts of the Northwest Territories, it said.             Reuter&#3;